### L3 — Roaming: Import a roaming token into a new session
### SPEC §8.4
### The roaming_token from example 03 is presented to the mobile gateway.
### The gateway may run on a completely different server, different LLM router,
### different database — SBP is server-agnostic. The session is fully restored.

POST /v1/sbp/sessions/import HTTP/1.1
Host: mobile-gateway.example.com
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <your-api-key>

{
  "roaming_token":   "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...<signature>",
  "target_agent_id": null,
  "allow_reuse":     false
}

### Response — HTTP 201
### A new session is created with all 24 messages replayed,
### memory restored (if schema_id is recognized), and state snapshot rehydrated.

HTTP/1.1 201 Created
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "session_id":    "d4e5f6a7-b8c9-0123-defa-234567890123",
  "session_token": "tok_mobile_abc456",
  "agent_id":      "agent_tokyo_planner",
  "step_count":    24,
  "message_count": 24,
  "provenance": {
    "imported_from": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "export_id":     "c3d4e5f6-a7b8-9012-cdef-123456789012"
  }
}
